 would guess that most of the parents who send their children to private schools don't even live in a neighborhood where the schools are bad in the first place.  Personally I think that's the right and the privilege of being a person who can afford it.  Who is she to tell people they are &quot;bad&quot; because they send their children to private school?  It's outrageous!!  And what about home schooling?  Would she be against that as well?   Lastly, I TOTALLY agree with the person who said...&quot;where are the parents of the children already going there?  why aren't they making the school better?&quot;  And therein lies the problem...many of today's parents are more involved in their own lives than in their children's lives.  And those that ARE involved are spread thin trying to make a living and keep their head above water.    Please.  Get real, lady and go peddle your socialist agenda somewhere else! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1204" language="en" documentId="2745" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Seralynn Lewis" date="Aug 29, 2013 8:21PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="21" thumbsDown="0" origId="2745" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1204"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>